at%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222956%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKids%20of%20the%201%25%20are%20twice%20as%20likely%20to%20get%20into%20'Ivy%20Plus'%20colleges%2C%20even%20when%20their%20grades%20are%20no%20better%20than%20anyone%20else's.%3Cp%3ECharles%20Krupa%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20new%20study%20shows%20kids%20of%20the%20top%201%25%20are%20over%20twice%20as%20likely%20to%20be%20admitted%20to%20Ivy%20Plus%20colleges.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThat's%20despite%20scoring%20no%20better%20than%20students%20of%20other%20income%20groups%2C%20per%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopportunityinsights.org%2Fpaper%2Fcollegeadmissions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpportunity%20Insights%3C%2Fa%3E%20study.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAfter%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3Dinsider%2Brace%2Baffirmative%2Baction%26oq%3Dinsider%2Brace%2Baffirmative%2Baction%26gs_lcrp%3DEgZjaHJvbWUyBggAEEUYOTIICAEQABgWGB4yCAgCEAAYFhgeMggIAxAAGBYYHjIICAQQABgWGB4yCAgFEAAYFhgeMgoIBhAAGIYDGIoFMgoIBxAAGIYDGIoFMgoICBAAGIYDGIoF0gEINDIwMmowajeoAgCwAgA%26sourceid%3Dchrome%26ie%3DUTF-8%5C%22%3Eend%20of%20race-based%20affirmative%20action%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20wealth%20and%20legacy%20admissions%20may%20now%20be%20the%20new%20focus%20of%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EChildren%20of%20the%20top%201%25%20of%20income%20earners%20are%20more%20than%20twice%20as%20likely%20to%20be%20admitted%20to%20Ivy%20Plus%20colleges%2C%20despite%20scoring%20no%20better%20on%20SAT%20or%20ACTs%20than%20students%20of%20other%20income%20groups%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopportunityinsights.org%2Fpaper%2Fcollegeadmissions%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%20study%20published%20on%20Monday%20by%20Opportunity%20Insights%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20group%20of%20Harvard-based%20economists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIvy%20Plus%20refers%20to%20the%20eight%20Ivy%20League%20colleges%20Brown%2C%20Columbia%2C%20Cornell%2C%20Dartmouth%2C%20Harvard%2C%20UPenn%2C%20Princeton%2C%20and%20Yale%2C%20plus%20Stanford%2C%20MIT%2C%20Duke%2C%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20study%2C%20roughly%2040%25%20of%20the%20wealthiest%20students%20with%2099th%20percentile%20SAT%20or%20ACT%20scores%20attend%20Ivy%20Plus%20colleges%20%E2%80%94%20double%20the%20rate%20of%20their%20equally%20qualified%20but%20poorer%20peers%20and%20four%20times%20that%20of%20middle-income%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20analyzed%20standardized%20test%20scores%20from%202001%20to%202015%2C%20parental%20tax%20records%20of%20nearly%20all%20college%20students%20from%201999%20to%202015%2C%20as%20well%20as%20internal%20admissions%20records%20from%20three%20of%20the%2012%20Ivy%20Plus%20colleges.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20identifies%20three%20main%20factors%20behind%20the%20discrepancy%3A%20a%20bias%20towards%20children%20of%20alumni%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20legacy%20students%20%E2%80%94%20wealthy%20students%20having%20higher%20non-academic%20ratings%2C%20and%20well-to-do%20students%20being%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20recruited%20as%20student-athletes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20noted%20that%20although%20less%20than%201%25%20of%20Americans%20attend%20these%2012%20colleges%2C%20these%20schools%20have%20an%20outsized%20impact.%20Ivy%20Plus%20graduates%20%26quot%3Baccount%20for%2015%25%20of%20those%20in%20the%20top%200.1%25%20of%20the%20income%20distribution%2C%20a%20quarter%20of%20US%20Senators%2C%20half%20of%20all%20Rhodes%20scholars%2C%20and%20three-fourths%20of%20Supreme%20Court%20justices%20appointed%20in%20the%20last%20half-century%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20findings%20come%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-ends-affirmative-action-colleges-decision-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhich%20effectively%20ended%20race-based%20affirmative%20action%20in%20June%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Insider%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20scrutiny%20from%20lawmakers%20and%20civil%20rights%20groups%20might%20be%20shifting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fhomenews%2Feducation%2F4084026-attention-turns-to-legacy-admissions-after-affirmative-action-ruling%2F%5C%22%3Etowards%20wealth%20and%20legacy%20admissions%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20their%20impact%20on%20inequality%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fsupreme-court-affirmative-action-legacy-college-admissions-5d6f34a13045752c6a37db67c66c7d63%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Associated%20Press%20reported%20on%20July%201.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Education%20launched%20a%20federal%20civil%20rights%20probe%20against%20Harvard%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fharvard-faces-federal-civil-rights-probe-over-legacy-admissions-2023-07-25%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealleging%20favoritism%20towards%20legacy%20students%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20their%20admission%20process%2C%20per%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ivy%20Plus%20colleges%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Insider%2C%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealthy-students-admission-ivy-league-plus-colleges-bias-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690350901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c082a91f17bb00196e2823%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealthy-students-admission-ivy-league-plus-colleges-bias-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20July%20report%20by%2