ntertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fkiara-advani-stuns-in-pink-and-gives-barbie-vibe-as-she-walks-the-ramp-gets-flying-kisses-from-sidharth-malhotras-mother%2Farticleshow%2F102127396.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102127396.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EKiara%20Advani%20was%20in%20Delhi%20as%20she%20walked%20the%20ramp%20and%20since%20Sidharth%20Malhotra's%20family%20stays%20in%20Delhi%2C%20his%20mother%20came%20to%20cheer%20for%20her%20'doting%20bahu'.%20She%20was%20seen%20showering%20flying%20kisses%20on%20Kiara%20as%20she%20walked%20the%20ramp.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Unlimited%20Powers%20to%20Harass'%3A%20Ex%20Civil%20Servants%20Criticise%20Modi%20Govt's%20Changes%20to%20Service%20Rules%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F26104436%2Fdaniel-alvasd-NItozEcUPrw-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20group%20of%2094%20former%20civil%20servants%20have%20released%20a%20statement%20expressing%20concerns%20over%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20changes%20to%20the%20All%20India%20Service%20Rules.%20These%20rules%2C%20the%20statement%20says%2C%20will%20make%20it%20impossible%20for%20public%20servants%20to%20express%20their%20opinions%20on%20matters%20of%20national%20importance.%20If%20they%20do%20not%20comply%2C%20their%20pensions%20may%20be%20revoked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20released%20under%20the%20umbrella%20of%20the%20Constitutional%20Conduct%20Group%2C%20the%20former%20civil%20servants%20have%20said%20that%20the%20proposed%20changes%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20be%20violative%20of%20Article%2051A%20of%20the%20Constitution%20which%20enjoins%20upon%20all%20citizens%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Echerish%20and%20follow%20the%20noble%20ideals%20that%20inspired%20the%20national%20struggle%20for%20freedom%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%20The%20right%20to%20criticise%20the%20government%20in%20power%20is%20part%20of%20these%20ideals%20and%20cannot%20be%20termed%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmisconduct%E2%80%9D%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CConsidering%20the%20severe%20penalties%20prescribed%20for%20misconduct%2C%20it%20is%20legally%20incumbent%20on%20the%20union%20government%20to%20have%20provided%20an%20exhaustive%20definition%20of%20the%20term.%20By%20leaving%20this%20deliberately%20vague%2C%20ambiguous%20and%20amorphous%2C%20the%20union%20government%20has%20armed%20itself%20with%20unlimited%20powers%20to%20harass%20and%20persecute%20any%20pensioner%20whose%20action%20is%20not%20to%20its%20liking%2C%20whether%20it%20be%C2%A0%20an%20article%2C%20an%20interview%2C%20participation%20in%20a%20protest%20march%20or%20seminar%2C%20or%20any%20form%20of%20criticism%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20full%20statement%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitutional%20Conduct%20Group%2C%20a%20collective%20of%20former%20civil%20servants%2C%20has%20noted%20with%20concern%20the%20recent%20amendments%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Personnel%2C%20Public%20Grievances%20and%20Pensioners%2C%20Govt.%20of%20India%2C%20to%20the%20All%20India%20Services%20(Death%20cum%20Retirement%20Benefits)%20Rules%201958%20(hereinafter%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20Rules).%20Through%20a%20notification%20dated%206.7.2023%2C%20these%20amendments%20have%2C%20%3Cem%3Einter%20alia%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20sought%20to%20impose%20a%20complete%20ban%20on%20the%20right%20of%20retired%20civil%20servants%20to%20comment%20on%20public%20matters%2C%20by%20threatening%20them%20with%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20their%20pensions.%20This%20would%20be%20violative%20of%20Article%2051A%20of%20the%20Constitution%20which%20enjoins%20upon%20all%20citizens%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Echerish%20and%20follow%20the%20noble%20ideals%20that%20inspired%20the%20national%20struggle%20for%20freedom%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%20The%20right%20to%20criticise%20the%20government%20in%20power%20is%20part%20of%20these%20ideals%20and%20cannot%20be%20termed%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmisconduct%E2%80%9D%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20original%20Rules%20of%201958%20(as%20amended%20from%20time%20to%20time)%20did%20contain%20a%20provision%20in%20Rule%203%20that%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Efuture%20good%20conduct%20shall%20be%20an%20implied%20condition%20of%20every%20grant%20of%20pension%20and%20its%20continuation%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20the%20pension%20could%20be%20withheld%20or%20withdrawn%2C%20in%20part%20or%20in%20full%2C%20if%20the%20pensioner%20is%20convicted%20of%20a%20serious%20crime%20or%20is%20held%20to%20be%20guilty%20of%20grave%20misconduct.%20However%2C%20such%20action%20could%20only%20be%20taken%20by%20the%20union%20government%20on%20a%20reference%20from%20the%20state%20government%20(the%20cadre%20to%20which%20the%20officer%20belonged).%20But%20now%2C%20Rule%203%20has%20been%20amended%20to%20provide%20that%20such%20punitive%20action%20can%20be%20taken%20by%20the%20union%20government%20%E2%80%9C%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3Eeither%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20on%20a%20reference%20from%20the%20state%20government%20concerned%20%3Cstrong%3Eor%20otherwise%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%20This%2C%20we%20feel%2C%20violates%20the%20principles%20of%20federalism%20and%20confers%20draconian%20powers%20of%20oversight%20and%20overrule%20on%20the%20union%20government%20which%20is%20not%20in%20conformity%20with%20the%20duality%20of%20control%20envisaged%20in%20the%20All%20India%20Services%20structure.%20It%20will%20further%20expose%20officers%20in%20opposition%20ruled%20states%20to%20intimidation%20by%20the%20party%20in%20power%20at%20the%20centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20note%20with%20apprehension%20that%20nowhere%20in%20the%20Rules%20has%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cgood%20conduct%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cgrave%20misconduct%E2%80%9D%20been%20defined%2C%20other%20than%20in%20sub-rule%208%20of%20Rule%203%20which%20merely%20%E2%80%9Cincludes%E2%80%9D%20disclosure%20of%20any%20information%20covered%20by%20the%20Official%20Secrets%20Act%20as%20a%20grave%20misconduct.%20Other%20than%20this%2C%20however%2C%20the%20Rules%20are%20completely%20silent%20on%20this%20issue%2C%20and%20everything%20is%20left%20to%20the%20decision%20or%20interpretation%20of%20the%20central%20government.%20Considering%20the%20severe%20penalties%20prescribed%20for%20misconduct%2C%20it%20is%20legally%20incumbent%20on%20the%20union%20government%20to%20have%20provided%20an%20exhaustive%20definition%20of%20the%20term.%20By%20leaving%20this%20deliberately%20vague%2C%20ambiguous%20and%20amorphous%2C%20the%20union%20government%20has%20armed%20itself%20with%20unlimited%20powers%20to%20harass%20and%20persecute%20any%20pensioner%20whose%20action%20is%20not%20to%20its%20liking%2C%20whether%20it%20be%C2%A0%20an%20article%2C%20an%20interview%2C%20participation%20in%20a%20protest%20march%20or%20seminar%2C%20or%20any%20form%20of%20criticism.%20In%20effect%2C%20this%20will%20totally%20muzzle%20and%20silence%20anyone%20who%20draws%20a%20pension%20from%20the%20state%2C%20which%20appears%20to%20be%20the%20intention%20behind%20these%20amendments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20withdrawal%2Fwithholding%20of%20pension%20for%20any%20criminal%20conviction%20is%20equally%20pernicious%20and%20untenable%20in%20law%20as%20it%20amounts%20to%20double%20jeopardy%2C%20punishing%20a%20person%20twice%20for%20the%20same%20offence.%20The%20pension%20is%20something%20(s)he%20has%20already%20earned%20by%20dint%20of%20long%20service.%20If%20(s)he%20commits%20a%20crime%2C%20(s)he%20will%20suffer%20the%20consequences%20of%20that%20by%20the%20operation%20of%20that%20criminal%20law%3A%20(s)he%20cannot%20be%20penalised%20a%20second%20time%20for%20the%20same%20offence%20by%20withdrawing%20her%2Fhis%20pension.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20law%20punishes%20the%20perpetrator%20of%20a%20crime%2C%20not%20her%2Fhis%20next%20of%20kin%3B%20by%20withdrawing%2Fwithholding%20her%2Fhis%20pension%20the%20government%20would%20be%20inflicting%20unjustified%20tribulations%20and%20misery%20on%20her%2Fhis%20family%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20both%20the%20original%20and%20the%20amended%20provision%20of%20Rule%203%20(except%20the%20newly%20introduced%20sub-rule%206%20about%20divulging%20secret%20and%20security%20related%20information)%20violate%20multiple%20rulings%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20various%20High%20Courts%20which%20have%2C%20over%20the%20last%2065%20years%2C%20constantly%20held%20that%20pension%20is%20an%20employee%E2%80%99s%20right%20and%20a%20kind%20of%20deferred%20payment%20for%20service%20already%20rendered.%20It%20is%20not%20largesse%20or%20charity%20bestowed%20by%20the%20government%20and%20does%20not%20depend%20upon%20the%20discretion%20of%20the%20government%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E(State%20of%20Punjab%20and%20Another%20vs%20Iqbal%20Singh)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDS%20Nakara%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%20(1983)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20that%20a%20law%20cannot%20discriminate%20between%20the%20same%20class%20of%20people%2C%20and%20that%20all%20statutes%20or%20laws%20must%20have%20some%20rational%20nexus%20with%20the%20object%20of%20the%20law.%20Rule%203%2C%20both%20the%20original%20and%20the%20amended%20versions%2C%20do%20not%20conform%20to%20these%20legal%20requirements.%20Pensioners%20are%20no%20longer%20government%20servants%3A%20they%20are%20free%20citizens%20of%20the%20country%20like%20any%20other%20citizen%2C%20with%20the%20same%20freedom%20of%20expression.%20By%20curbing%20this%20right%20under%20the%20specious%20guise%20of%20%E2%80%9Cgood%20conduct%E2%80%9D%20the%20government%20is%20discriminating%20against%20them%20and%2C%20therefore%2C%20also%20violating%20Article%2014%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Furthermore%2C%20what%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Cobject%E2%80%9D%20of%20this%20rule%2C%20if%20not%20to%20silence%20any%20form%20of%20criticism%20of%20the%20government%3F%20This%20cannot%20be%20held%20to%20be%20rational%2C%20reasonable%20or%20based%20on%20some%20valid%20principle%2C%20as%20is%20required%20in%20another%20judgment%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E(Ramana%20Dayaram%20Shetty%20vs%20The%20Airport%20Authority%20of%20India%20and%20Others)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERule%203%20has%20become%20obsolete%3A%20it%20is%20a%20legal%20anachronism%20which%20also%20militates%20against%20the%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20dissent.%20It%20makes%20pensioners%20bonded%20labourers%20for%20life%2C%20a%20separate-and%20inferior-class%20of%20citizens%20who%20do%20not%20enjoy%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression.%20It%20further%20seeks%20to%20impose%20the%20Conduct%20Rules%20(which%20apply%20only%20to%20those%20in%20service%20of%20the%20government)%20on%20pensioners%20through%20the%20back%20door%2C%20which%20is%20abhorrent%20in%20law%2C%20as%20the%20latter%20are%20no%20longer%20in%20service.%20They%20are%20free%20citizens%20and%20there%20exists%20no%20employer-employee%20relationship%20between%20them%20and%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERules%20governing%20conditions%20of%20service%20need%20to%20be%20dynamic%20and%20in%20sync%20with%20the%20changes%20in%20interpretation%20of%20laws%2C%20the%20evolution%20of%20jurisprudence%20on%20rights%20and%20freedoms%2C%20the%20development%20of%20the%20concepts%20of%20democracy%20and%20an%20open%20society.%20Rule%203%20fails%20to%20do%20so%2C%20is%20stuck%20in%20a%20time%20warp%20and%20needs%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitutional%20Conduct%20Group%20urges%20the%20governments%20in%20the%20states%20and%20the%20union%20government%20to%20review%20this%20rule%20with%20a%20view%20to%20abolishing%20it%2C%20and%20not%20to%20further%20build%20upon%20it.%20In%20the%20interim%20we%20further%20request%20the%20union%20government%20to%20hold%20in%20abeyance%20these%20amendments%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20federalism%2C%20fair%20play%2C%20equality%20of%20citizens%2C%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20a%20vibrant%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESATYAMEVA%20JAYATE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConstitutional%20Conduct%20Group%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E(94%20signatories)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%20width%3D%5C%22614%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2256%5C%22%3E1.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22123%5C%22%3EAnita%20Agnihotri%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2295%5C%22%3EIAS%20(Retd.)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22340%5C%22%3EFormer%20Secretary%2C%20Department%20of%20Social%20Justice%20Empowerment%2C%20GoI%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2256%5C%22%3E2.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22123%5C%22%3EAnand%20Arni%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2295%5C%22%3ERAS%20(Retd.)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22340%5C%22%3EFormer%20Special%20Secretary%2C%20Cabinet%20Secretariat%2C%20GoI%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2256%5C%22%3E3.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22123%5C%22%3EG.%20Balachandhran%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2295%5C%22%3EIAS%20(Retd.)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22340%5C%22%3EFormer%20Additional%20Chief%20Secretary%2C%20Govt.%20of%20West%20Bengal%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2256%5C%22%3E4.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22123%5C%22%3EVappala%20Balachandran%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2295%5C%22%3EIPS%20(Retd.)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22340%5C%22%3EFormer%20Special%20Secretary%2C%20Cabinet%20Secretariat%2C%20GoI%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2256%5C%22%3E5.%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22123%5C%22%3EChandrashekar%20Balakrishnan%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%2295%5C%22%3EIAS%20(Retd.)%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22340%5C%22