education%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20these%20children%20need%20camaraderie.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20disabled%20people%2C%20opportunities%20to%20interact%20with%20peers%20are%20few%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20is%20common%20to%20loop%20or%20keep%20children%20with%20disabilities%20together%2C%20with%20minimal%20interactions%20with%20a%20wider%20circle.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20need%20to%20open%20up%20these%20areas%20so%20children%20with%20disabilities%20are%20more%20visible.%20That%E2%80%99s%20where%20our%20children%E2%80%99s%20club%20Latika%20Vihar%2C%20where%20these%20children%20interact%20and%20play%2C%20helps.%20It%E2%80%99s%20wonderful%20how%20they%20grow%20up%20together%2C%20the%20simple%20and%20uncomplicated%20way%20they%20interact%20with%20each%20other.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20child%20grows%2C%20integration%20and%20mainstreaming%20get%20tougher.%20%E2%80%9CChildren%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20these%20boundaries%20of%20disparity%2C%20class%2C%20caste%2C%20race%E2%80%A6.%E2%80%9D%20Rupa%20notes.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20neurotypical%20children%20too%2C%20in%20the%20early%20years%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20natural%20to%20have%20other%20children%20in%20the%20classroom%20who%20are%20different%20from%20them.%20Teachers%20are%20also%20more%20accepting%20of%20children%20of%20this%20age%3B%20there%E2%80%99s%20more%20benefit%20of%20the%20doubt.%20If%20we%20send%20a%20disabled%20kid%20to%20school%20without%20specifying%20that%20label%20or%20giving%20them%20that%20assessment%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20that%20teachers%20work%20very%20hard%20to%20make%20that%20child%20adjust.%20And%20then%20the%20child%20does%20beautifully.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EEmbracing%20the%20%E2%80%98difference%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJo%20opines%20that%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20education%20system%20is%20its%20rigidity.%20%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%20an%20assumption%20that%20all%20children%20in%20the%20classroom%20learn%20the%20same%20way.%20We%20see%20how%20that%20fails%20so%20many%20kids%20who%20are%20already%20in%20school.%20When%20you%20bring%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F296192%2Fshraddha-soparkar-provides-free-therapy-to-children-with-disabilities-madhuram-charitable-trust%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisabled%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20the%20mix%2C%20this%20becomes%20more%20apparent.%20The%20blame%20is%20put%20on%20the%20children%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20those%20with%20disabilities%2C%20but%20also%20those%20who%20have%20a%20different%20way%20of%20learning.%20We%20label%20them%20as%20%E2%80%98naughty%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98lazy%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98not%20interested%E2%80%99%E2%80%A6The%20system%20is%20designed%20in%20a%20way%20to%20exclude%20at%20multiple%20levels.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%E2%80%99s%20a%20very%20academic%2C%20literal%20way%20of%20learning%2C%20when%20the%20fact%20is%20that%20children%20universally%20learn%20better%20by%20doing.%20This%20idea%20is%20not%20even%20well%20understood%2C%20let%20alone%20implemented.%20If%20we%20cater%20to%20this%20difference%20in%20ways%20of%20learning%2C%20we%20will%20automatically%20move%20towards%20more%20inclusivity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERupa%20emphasises%20on%20a%20social-emotional%20learning%20(SEL)%20curriculum.%20This%20is%20a%20process%20by%20which%20a%20child%20learns%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F285570%2Fchild-sexual-abuse-survivor-circles-of-safety-sexuality-education-school-curriculum%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderstand%2C%20express%2C%20and%20manage%20emotions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20is%20focused%20on%20helping%20them%20build%20healthy%20relationships%2C%20manage%20positive%20and%20negative%20feelings%2C%20and%20develop%20a%20sense%20of%20empathy%20and%20right%20or%20wrong.%20%E2%80%9C