%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20grandfather%2C%20state%20founder%20Kim%20Il%20Sung%2C%20took%20the%20reins%20of%20the%20country%20with%20Soviet%20support.%20Now%2C%20as%20North%20Korea%20prepares%20to%20mark%20the%2070th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20armistice%20that%20ended%20the%20Korean%20War%20on%20July%2027%2C%201953%2C%20it's%20once%20again%20Russia%20the%20regime%20must%20thank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20resumed%20sending%20oil%20to%20North%20Korea%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%202020%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20said%20last%20month.%20That%20follows%20an%20earlier%20restart%20of%20grain%20shipments.%20While%20it's%20impossible%20to%20know%20what%20is%20going%20in%20the%20other%20direction%2C%20both%20the%20US%20government%20and%20independent%20analysts%20have%20one%20main%20thesis%3A%20munitions%20from%20North%20Korea's%20vast%20stockpiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20interventions%2C%20of%20course%2C%20aren't%20sufficient%20to%20restore%20a%20tattered%2C%20isolated%20economy%20to%20full%20health.%20Yet%20together%20with%20the%20reopening%20of%20trade%20links%20with%20China%20and%20other%20sources%20of%20income%20like%20cybercrime%2C%20the%20assistance%20from%20Russia%20is%20ensuring%20the%20economy%20remains%20stable%20enough%20to%20function%2C%20enabling%20Kim%20to%20continue%20defying%20the%20international%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNorth%20Korea%20always%20manages%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20survive%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rachel%20Minyoung%20Lee%2C%20a%20regional%20issues%20manager%20at%20the%20Vienna-based%20Open%20Nuclear%20Network%20who%20worked%20as%20an%20analyst%20for%20the%20CIA's%20Open%20Source%20Enterprise%20for%20almost%20two%20decades.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20indication%20that%20it%20would%20return%20to%20nuclear%20talks%20anytime%20soon.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20and%20China%20are%20showing%20their%20support%20for%20Kim%20by%20sending%20high-profile%20delegations%20to%20North%20Korea%20to%20mark%20the%20anniversary%20-%20the%20first%20such%20visits%20by%20foreign%20envoys%20since%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic.%20The%20Russian%20group%20arrived%20Tuesday%20night%20and%20received%20a%20welcome%20from%20top%20cadres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMunitions%20Math%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPyongyang%2C%20which%20has%20been%20banned%20from%20arms%20sales%20for%20about%2015%20years%2C%20rejects%20accusations%20it%20is%20supplying%20Russia.%20Yet%20the%20White%20House%20in%20December%20said%20it%20had%20evidence%20North%20Korea%20completed%20an%20initial%20arms%20shipment%20to%20the%20Wagner%20Group%20for%20use%20in%20Ukraine%20that%20included%20infantry%20rockets%20and%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20item%20that%20North%20Korea%20has%20and%20Russia%20likely%20wants%20is%20152%20mm%20artillery%20shells.%20These%20are%20interoperable%20with%20the%20Soviet-era%20weaponry%20that's%20been%20pushed%20back%20into%20service%20in%20Ukraine.%20The%20Kremlin's%20war%20machine%20has%20been%20burning%20through%20thousands%20daily%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Jamestown%20Foundation%20research%20group%2C%20and%20has%20been%20scrambling%20for%20supplies%20as%20the%20conflict%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20Korea%20possesses%20untold%20stores%20of%20munitions%20that%20could%20run%20into%20millions%20of%20rounds%20for%20an%20arsenal%20that%20has%20for%20decades%20held%20Seoul%20under%20the%20threat%20of%20devastation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20Korea%20would%20likely%20jump%20at%20the%20chance%20to%20offload%20some%20of%20its%20stockpile%20at%20a%20hefty%20price%2C%20said%20weapons%20expert%20Joost%20Oliemans%2C%20who%20co-authored%20the%20book%20The%20Armed%20Forces%20of%20North%20Korea.%20Exactly%20how%20much%20they'd%20get%20would%20be%20down%20to%20their%20ability%20to%20negotiate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20North%20Korea%20sold%20shells%20at%20%241%2C000%20each%2C%20selling%20250%2C000%20would%20be%20equal%20to%20about%201%25%20of%20its%20GDP%2C%20according%20to%20Bloomberg%20News%20calculations.%20That's%20a%20conservative%20estimate%20because%20high%20demand%20has%20driven%20up%20prices%2C%20with%20the%20155%20mm%20shells%20used%20by%20NATO%20forces%20priced%20at%20about%20%243%2C000%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrade%20Signals%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20both%20North%20Korea%20and%20Russia%20are%20subject%20to%20UN%20sanctions%2C%20both%20seek%20to%20conceal%20exactly%20how%20much%20trade%20is%20going%20on.%20But%20there%20are%20numerous%20signs%20that%20activity%20is%20picking%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20late%202022%2C%20the%20two%20countries%20restored%20a%20rail%20link%20that%20had%20been%20suspended%20for%20nearly%20three%20years%2C%20according%20to%20satellite%20images%20including%20those%20from%20November%20that%20show%20a%20train%20crossing%20from%20Russia%20into%20North%20Korea%20and%20stopping%20at%20a%20freight%20handling%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKang%20Mi-jin%2C%20a%20North%20Korean%20defector%20who%20now%20runs%20a%20company%20in%20South%20Korea%20that%20watches%20the%20economy%20of%20her%20former%20home%2C%20says%20that%20her%20contacts%20report%20that%20Russian%20sugar%20has%20made%20its%20way%20into%20markets%20in%20recent%20months.%20It's%20been%20warily%20received%20since%20it's%20coarser%20and%20a%20darker%20color%20than%20what%20North%20Koreans%20are%20used%20to%2C%20Kang%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20indications%20of%20increased%20activity%20with%20China%20after%20the%20two%20countries%20reopened%20their%20main%20rail%20link%20last%20year%20that%20had%20been%20closed%20since%20Covid.%20Traffic%20between%20the%20Chinese%20border%20city%20of%20Dandong%20and%20North%20Korea's%20nearby%20city%20of%20Sinuiju%20can%20be%20watched%20on%20the%20streets%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Daily%20NK%20website%2C%20part%20of%20a%20group%20of%20not-for-profit%20agencies%20affiliated%20with%20the%20South%20Korean%20Unification%20Ministry%2C%20said%20its%20sources%20on%20the%20ground%20have%20seen%20the%20length%20of%20freight%20trains%20increasing.%20It%20reports%20that%20foodstuffs%20and%20building%20materials%20are%20among%20the%20items%20making%20their%20way%20into%20North%20Korea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20nearly%20impossible%20to%20see%20is%20activity%20in%20a%20pipeline%20between%20the%20two%20cities%20that%20was%20exempt%20from%20sanctions%20and%20could%20be%20supplying%20as%20much%20as%20750%2C000%20tons%20(5.5%20million%20barrels)%20of%20oil%20annually%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20from%20specialists%20David%20von%20Hippel%20and%20Peter%20Hayes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20Signs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20few%20items%20North%20Korea%20tries%20to%20sell%20abroad%20are%20commodities%20it%20can%20mine%20at%20home%20and%20then%20trade%20in%20ways%20that%20evade%20interception.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20main%20international%20seaport%20of%20Nampo%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20shipping%20detectable%20by%20the%20outside%20world%20reached%20100%20vessels%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20this%20year%20and%20was%20on%20pace%20to%20triple%20the%20traffic%20the%20port%20had%20seen%20during%20the%20pandemic%20years%2C%20data%20from%20IHS%20Markit%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20further%20sign%20that%20North%20Korea%20has%20money%20to%20spend%2C%20a%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Panel%20of%20Experts%20report%20said%20in%20March%20that%20deliveries%20of%20refined%20petroleum%20products%20in%202022%20again%20exceeded%20the%20500%2C000%20barrel%20yearly%20amount%20of%20imports%20allowed%20under%20sanctions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22ug0npu28%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fug0npu28_russiasouth-korea-trade-chart_625x300_26_July_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20the%20panel%20said%2C%20North%20Korea%20has%20also%20acquired%20six%20more%20cargo%20vessels%20in%20a%20violation%20of%20sanctions.%20Four%20of%20these%20ships%20were%20among%20a%20dozen%20that%20sailed%20to%20destinations%20for%20iron%20and%20coal%20in%20China%20over%20the%20past%20month%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20sell%20commodities%20mined%20in%20North%20Korea%20for%20hard%20currency%2C%20NK%20News%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EData%20from%20Bloomberg%20shows%20that%20five%20of%20the%20vessels%20identified%20by%20the%20UN%20have%20docked%20at%20least%20once%20in%20China%20since%20March.%20Vessel%20data%20showed%20multiple%20trips%20to%20a%20grain%20elevator%20berth%20near%20Dalian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22mlp7kkqg%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fmlp7kkqg_russiasouth-korea-trade-chart_625x300_26_July_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20Korea%20has%20also%20continued%20to%20dodge%20sanctions%20through%20the%20ship-to-ship%20transfer%20of%20commodities%20on%20the%20high%20seas%20often%20done%20in%20darkness%20with%20transponders%20turned%20off%20to%20avoid%20detection%2C%20the%20UN%20panel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20likely%20source%20of%20income%20is%20cybercrime.%20Both%20the%20US%20and%20South%20Korea%20have%20accused%20Kim's%20regime%20of%20deploying%20hackers%20to%20various%20corners%20of%20the%20world%20to%20fund%20its%20weapons%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20say%20these%20in-demand%20workers%20can%20make%20as%20much%20as%20%24300%2C000%20a%20year%20abroad%20-%20often%20remotely%20through%20freelance%20platforms%20with%20falsified%20or%20stolen%20identification%20-%20and%20can%20assist%20in%20enabling%20cyber%20attacks%20and%20cryptocurrency%20thefts%20that%20helped%20North%20Korea%20earn%20an%20estimated%20%241.7%20billion%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPutting%20It%20Together%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20Korea%20releases%20no%20official%20statistics%20on%20the%20size%20of%20its%20overall%20economy.%20With%20so%20much%20off%20the%20books%20and%20deliberately%20obscured%2C%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20make%20overall%20assessments%20about%20the%20amount%20of%20economic%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20the%20country%20is%20still%20suffering%20from%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20countries%20in%20the%20world%20not%20to%20have%20started%20a%20vaccination%20program%2C%20said%20Anwita%20Basu%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20North%20Korea%20and%20head%20of%20Europe%20country%20risk%20at%20BMI%2C%20a%20Fitch%20Solutions%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20signs%20of%20a%20resumption%20of%20trade%20with%20China%2C%20historically%20North%20Korea's%20biggest%20trading%20partner%2C%20means%20Fitch%20estimate%20the%20economy%20returned%20to%20growth%20after%20two%20full%20years%20of%20contraction%2C%20though%20significant%20uncertainties%20remain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22bgbsgiu8%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fbgbsgiu8_russiasouth-korea-trade-chart_625x300_26_July_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20outlook%20for%20the%20North%20Korean%20economy%20is%20murky%2C%26quot%3B%20Basu%20said.%20Still%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20anticipate%20that%20the%20economy%20will%20remain%20sufficiently%20stable%20to%20enable%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20to%20remain%20in%20power.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20conditions%20on%20the%20ground%20in%20North%20Korea%20remain%20bleak%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20population.%20The%20World%20Food%20Programme%2C%20which%20had%20been%20on%20the%20ground%20in%20North%20Korea%20for%20years%20until%20the%20pandemic%2C%20estimates%20that%2040%25%20of%20the%20population%20is%20undernourished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFlooding%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%20has%20devastated%20farm%20land%20and%20wiped%20out%20crops%2C%20while%20Kim's%20decision%20to%20shut%20the%20borders%20cut%20off%20a%20flow%20of%20foodstuffs%20that%20made%20their%20way%20to%20markets.%20The%20WFP%20is%20no%20longer%20distributing%20food%2C%20raising%20worries%20about%20a%20possible%20return%20to%20the%20famine%20of%20the%20late%201990s%20that%20some%20estimates%20said%20killed%20as%20many%20as%203.5%20million%20people%20over%20a%20number%20of%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESelf-Reliance%20Doctrine%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKim's%20state%20propaganda%20machine%20still%20leans%20heavily%20on%20a%20self-reliance%20doctrine%20forged%20by%20his%20grandfather%20calling%20on%20its%20citizens%20to%20help%20one%20another%20in%20the%20face%20of%20what%20it%20sees%20as%20the%20hostile%20intents%20of%20the%20US%20to%20cripple%20its%20economy%20and%20topple%20its%20rulers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20investment%20in%20big-ticket%20items%20such%20as%20power%20plant%20construction%20have%20faltered%20after%20sanctions%20were%20tightened%20in%202017%20to%20halt%20the%20import%20of%20machinery%2C%20Kim's%20government%20has%20stepped%20up%20other%20symbolic%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state-run%20Korean%20Central%20News%20Agency%20has%20mentioned%20%26quot%3Bhousing%20construction%26quot%3B%20about%20200%20times%20in%20about%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20according%20to%20a%20database%20search.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKim%20%26quot%3Bhas%20become%20the%20great%20pioneer%20and%20creator%20for%20realizing%20the%20socialist%20ideal%20to%20devote%20himself%20to%20building%20the%20people's%20paradise%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20KCNA%20said%20when%20Kim%20attended%20a%20ground-breaking%20ceremony%20in%20February%20punctuated%20by%20fireworks%20and%20cheers%20from%20the%20masses%20for%20a%20project%20to%20build%2010%2C000%20new%20apartments%20in%20Pyongyang.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20costs%2C%20though%2C%20pale%20compared%20to%20the%20money%20spent%20on%20armaments.%20Kim's%20regime%20spent%20an%20estimated%20%24400%20million%20to%20%24650%20million%20to%20build%20and%20test%20the%2033%20missiles%20it%20fired%20off%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%202022%2C%20data%20compiled%20by%20the%20Korea%20Institute%20for%20Defense%20Analyses%2C%20a%20government-affiliated%20military%20research%20center%2C%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20ended%20up%20shooting%20off%20more%20than%2070%20that%20year%2C%20meaning%20it%20could%20have%20spent%20more%20than%20%241%20billion%20for%20missiles%20tested.%20That%20is%20equal%20to%20about%204%25%20of%20its%20%2425%20billion%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%2C%20South%20Korea%20and%20Japan%20have%20said%20Kim%20would%20be%20better%20off%20using%20the%20money%20spent%20on%20missiles%20to%20feed%20his%20people.%20But%20Kim's%20defiance%20of%20the%20international%20community%20has%20gained%20him%20some%20measure%20of%20security%20against%20the%20risk%20of%20any%20US%20action.%20His%20weapons%20program%20has%20evolved%20to%20a%20point%20that%20he%20could%20have%20enough%20in%20his%20arsenal%20to%20deliver%20a%20credible%20nuclear%20strike%20on%20South%20Korea%20and%20Japan%20-%20the%20two%20Asian%20nations%20that%20host%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20US%20military%20personnel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20he%20is%20showing%20no%20signs%20of%20slowing%20down.%20Following%202022's%20record-breaking%20series%20of%20tests%2C%20Kim%20has%20again%20ramped%20up%20his%20military%20program%20this%20year.%20Just%20this%20month%2C%20he%20tested%20a%20new%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missile%20designed%20to%20strike%20the%20US%20mainland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%228r0gv0bo%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2F8r0gv0bo_russiasouth-korea-trade-chart_625x300_26_July_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRussia's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20likely%20emboldening%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20to%20behave%20more%20aggressively%2C''%20said%20Duyeon%20Kim%2C%20an%20adjunct%20senior%20fellow%20in%20Seoul%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20a%20New%20American%20Security.%20%26quot%3BChina%20and%20Russia%20have%20both%2