vative%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22LeBron's%20son%20stable%20after%20suffering%20cardiac%20arrest%20in%20practice%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690342170000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102123300%2Cimgsize-63548.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Foff-the-field%2Flebron-james-son-stable-after-suffering-cardiac-arrest-during-college-basketball-practice%2Farticleshow%2F102122976.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bronny%20James%2C%20the%20eldest%20son%20of%20NBA%20star%20LeBron%20James%2C%20suffered%20a%20cardiac%20arrest%20during%20a%20college%20basketball%20practice%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%20He%20collapsed%20on%20the%20floor%20during%20training%20with%20his%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%20teammates.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Foff-the-field%2Flebron-james-son-stable-after-suffering-cardiac-arrest-during-college-basketball-practice%2Farticleshow%2F102122976.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20Probe%20Opened%20Over%20Harvard%20University's%20%5C%22Legacy%20Admissions%5C%22%20Policy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Education%20has%20opened%20a%20civil%20rights%20investigation%20into%20Harvard%20University's%20policy%20of%20giving%20family%20members%20of%20former%20students%20and%20donors%20preference%20in%20admissions%20decisions%2C%20documents%20showed%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20probe%20into%20the%20prestigious%20university's%20so-called%20%26quot%3Blegacy%20admissions%26quot%3B%20policy%2C%20a%20practice%20used%20by%20many%20colleges%20across%20the%20United%20States%2C%20comes%20less%20than%20a%20month%20after%20a%20major%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20banned%20the%20use%20of%20race%20in%20college%20application%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20decision%2C%20in%20which%20Harvard%20was%20also%20one%20of%20the%20targets%2C%20prompted%20fresh%20debate%20over%20the%20fairness%20of%20admissions%20policies%20at%20America's%20top%20universities%2C%20and%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20those%20policies%20contribute%20to%20inequities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20probe%20by%20the%20Education%20Department's%20civil%20rights%20wing%20is%20in%20response%20to%20a%20complaint%20filed%20by%20three%20organizations%20representing%20minority%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20argue%20that%20due%20to%20Harvard's%20historically%20white%20student%20body%2C%20legacy%20admissions%20pulling%20from%20alumni%20discriminate%20against%20minority%20applicants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20complaint%2C%20the%20groups%20argue%20that%20nearly%2070%20percent%20of%20Harvard%20applicants%20with%20family%20connections%20or%20links%20to%20donors%20are%20white.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20boost%20that%20the%20predominately%20white%20applicants%20receive%20from%20Donor%20and%20Legacy%20Preferences%20is%20substantial%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20groups%20said%20in%20their%20complaint%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20recent%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20increased%20the%20importance%20of%20%26quot%3Brooting%20out%20preferences%20that%20unjustifiably%20disadvantage%20applicants%20of%20color.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20groups%20posted%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20Education%20Department's%20letter%20to%20Harvard%20stating%20that%20a%20civil%20rights%20inquiry%20had%20been%20opened.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhite%20House%20Press%20Secretary%20Karine%20Jean-Pierre%2C%20while%20not%20wanting%20to%20comment%20directly%20on%20the%20investigation%2C%20said%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20is%20generally%20opposed%20to%20legacy%20admissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20has%20made%20clear%20%26quot%3Bthat%20legacy%20admissions%20hold%20back%20our%20ability%20to%20build%20diverse%20student%20bodies%2C%26quot%3B%20Jean-Pierre%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20reached%20for%20comment%20by%20AFP%2C%20Harvard%20did%20not%20address%20the%20Education%20Department%20probe%20directly%2C%20saying%20only%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20process%20of%20reviewing%20aspects%20of%20our%20admissions%20policies%26quot%3B%20following%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20decision%20on%20the%20use%20of%20race%20in%20admissions%2C%20known%20as%20affirmative%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20case%2C%20the%20court%20sided%20with%20an%20activist%20group%2C%20Students%20for%20Fair%20Admissions%2C%20that%20sued%20the%20oldest%20private%20and%20public%20institutions%20of%20higher%20education%20in%20the%20country%20--%20Harvard%20and%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%20(UNC)%20--%20over%20their%20admissions%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20claimed%20that%20race-conscious%20admissions%20policies%20in%20effect%20discriminated%20against%20Asian%20Americans%20competing%20to%20enter%20the%20two%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarvard%20and%20UNC%2C%20like%20a%20number%20of%20other%20competitive%20US%20schools%2C%20considered%20an%20applicant's%20race%20or%20ethnicity%20as%20a%20factor%20to%20ensure%20a%20diverse%20student%20body%20and%20representation%20of%20minorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20affirmative%20action%20policies%20arose%20from%20the%20civil%20rights%20movement%20in%20the%201960s%2C%20aiming%20to%20help%20address%20the%20legacy%20of%20discrimination%20against%20African%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690342080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2021-12%2F2c1n352k_harvard-university-facebook_625x300_16_December_21.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-probe-opened-over-harvard-universitys-legacy-admissions-policy-4240290