he%20law%20in%20speaking%20to%20Western%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20how%20Russia's%20war%20is%20impacting%20its%20own%20people%20in%20devastating%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20war%20began%20in%20February%202022%2C%20Russia%20has%20recruited%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20prisoners%20to%20join%20its%20ranks%2C%20offering%20them%20a%20chance%20at%20freedom%20in%20return%20for%20their%20service.%20But%20Russia%20has%20often%20used%20these%20poorly-trained%20soldiers%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdrafted-russian-soldiers-dying-within-a-matter-of-days-2022-10%5C%22%3Ecannon%20fodder%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-russia-uses-infantry-and-mercenaries-for-attacks-in-ukraine-2023-5%5C%22%3Edisposable%20infantry%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20amid%20the%20brutal%20battle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tactic%20was%20first%20employed%20exclusively%20by%20the%20mercenary%20Wagner%20Group%2C%20but%20the%20official%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-copies-wagner-prisoner-recruitment-10000-signed-up-april-uk-2023-5%5C%22%3ERussian%20Defense%20Ministry%20copied%20Wagner's%20playbook%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20signing%20at%20least%2010%2C000%20convicts%20to%20the%20war%20effort%20in%20the%20month%20of%20April%20alone%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDefenceHQ%2Fstatus%2F1656535955338063873%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20UK%20intelligence.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20recruit%2C%20Andrei%2C%20went%20to%20prison%20when%20he%20was%2020%20years%20old%20on%20minor%20drug%20charges%2C%20his%20mother%2C%20Yulia%2C%20told%20CNN.%20He%20was%20given%20a%20nine-and-a-half-year%20sentence%20and%20had%20served%20just%20three%20years%20when%20the%20opportunity%20for%20freedom%20presented%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20didn't%20remember%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20he%20was%20offered%2C%20said%20he%20hadn't%20checked.%20So%2C%20I%20didn't%20see%20any%20financial%20interest%20for%20him.%20It%20was%20just%20about%20freedom%2C%26quot%3B%20Yulia%20told%20the%20outlet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYulia%20said%20her%2023-year-old%20son%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20yet%20a%20man%26quot%3B%20when%20he%20left%20his%20prison%20cell%20and%20headed%20toward%20his%20death.%20During%20his%20brief%20training%2C%20Andrei%20sent%20his%20mother%20short%20videos%20and%20voice%20recordings%2C%20joking%20about%20the%20weather%20and%20documenting%20his%20preparations.%20Yulia%20provided%20video%20proof%20and%20chat%20messages%20with%20her%20son%20to%20verify%20her%20story%2C%20CNN%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20May%208%2C%20Andrei%20messaged%20his%20mother%20and%20said%20his%20unit%20was%20officially%20being%20sent%20to%20the%20eastern%20front%20lines%20ahead%20of%20a%20dawn%20assault%20the%20following%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20arguing.%20It%20is%20horrible%20to%20say%2C%20but%20I%20already%20thought%20of%20him%20like%20he%20was%20dead%2C%26quot%3B%20Yulia%20told%20CNN.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20day%20I%20told%20him%20'no%2C%20no%2C%20no.'%20And%20he%20didn't%20listen%20to%20me.%20When%20he%20said%2C%20'we're%20going%20to%20storm%2C'%20I%20wrote%20him%20'Run%2C%20Forrest%2C%20Run.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20last%20time%20they%20spoke.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20intervening%20weeks%2C%20Yulia%20said%20she%20spoke%20to%20relatives%20of%20other%20convict%20soldiers%20who%20were%20recruited%20from%20his%20same%20penal%20colony%20who%20said%20as%20many%20as%2060%20Russian%20soldiers%20died%20in%20the%20May%209%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20CNN%20nor%20Insider%20were%20able%20to%20independently%20verify%20her%20claims.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYulia%20told%20the%20outlet%20that%20she%20still%20hasn't%20received%20her%20son's%20body%20or%20any%20of%20his%20belongings.%20All%20she%20got%20was%20a%20letter%20from%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20which%20marked%20Andrei's%20d