ust%20look%20at%20poverty%20in%20terms%20of%20people%20who%20are%20financially%20poor%20%E2%80%93%20it%20examined%2012%20indicators%20that%20are%20clubbed%20under%20health%2C%20education%2C%20and%20standard%20of%20living%2C%20and%20measured%20the%20deprivation%20score%20of%20the%20people%20in%20these%20areas.%20Hence%2C%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98multidimensional%20poverty%E2%80%99%20is%20used%20in%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20following%20charts%2C%20we%20look%20at%20the%20five%20states%20with%20the%20lowest%20proportion%20of%20multidimensionally%20poor%20people%20and%20how%20they%20performed%20as%20per%20the%2012%20parameters%20%E2%80%93%20out%20of%20which%20ten%20are%20in%20consonance%20with%20the%20global%20multidimensional%20poverty%20index%20measured%20by%20the%20UN.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EHealth%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20indicators%20under%20the%20health%20category.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENutrition%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20household%20is%20considered%20deprived%20if%20any%20child%20between%20the%20ages%20of%200%20to%2059%20months%3B%20or%20a%20woman%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2015%20to%2049%20years%3B%20or%20a%20man%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2015%20to%2054%20years%20for%20whom%20nutritional%20information%20is%20available%20is%20found%20to%20be%20undernourished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20woman%20(15%20to%2049%20years)%20or%20a%20man%20(15%20to%2054%20years)%20is%20considered%20%E2%80%98undernourished%E2%80%99%20if%20their%20body%20mass%20index%20(BMI)%20is%20below%2018.5%20kg%2Fm2%20or%20the%20age-specific%20BMI%20cutoff%20for%20individuals%20aged%2015-19%20years%2C%20when%20information%20is%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChildren%20under%20five%20years%20of%20age%20are%20considered%20malnourished%20if%20their%20z-score%20of%20height-for-age%20(stunting)%20or%20weight-for-age%20(underweight)%20is%20below%20minus%20two%20standard%20deviations%20from%20the%20median%20of%20the%20reference%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20to%20be%20noted%20that%20even%20if%20a%20single%20member%20of%20the%20household%20is%20identified%20as%20%E2%80%98undernourished%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20entire%20household%20is%20treated%20as%20deprived%20of%20nutrition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20chart%20below%2C%20we%20have%20compared%20only%20those%20states%20where%20the%20extent%20of%20multidimensional%20poverty%20is%20lowest%20in%20India.%20However%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Manipur%2C%20and%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20have%20lesser%20proportions%20of%20population%20deprived%2C%20but%20more%20than%20Kerala%2C%20as%20far%20as%20nutrition%20is%20concerned.%20Similarly%2C%20Nagaland%20figures%20in%20between%20Punjab%20and%20Goa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FlkAfI%2F1%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Assessing%20states'%20nutrition%20deprivation%20(in%20%25)%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EChild%20and%20adolescent%20mortality%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20household%20is%20considered%20deprived%20if%20any%20child%20or%20adolescent%20under%2018%20years%20of%20age%20has%20died%20in%20the%20household%20in%20the%20five-year%20period%20preceding%20the%20survey%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%20It%20goes%20on%20to%20add%20that%20the%20death%20of%20a%20child%20or%20an%20adolescent%20signifies%20a%20%E2%80%98larger%20set%20of%20deprivations%20already%20experienced%20by%20the%20household%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELack%20of%20access%20to%20healthcare%2C%20infectious%20diseases%2C%20malnutrition%2C%20iron%20deficiency%20(anemia)%2C%20or%20an%20unsafe%20environment%20are%20contributors%20to%20child%20and%20adolescent%20mortality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20therefore%2C%20NITI%20Aayog%20says%20that%20the%20death%20of%20a%20child%20or%20an%20adolescent%20indicates%20the%20deprivations%20experienced%20by%20a%20household%20in%20one%20or%20more%20of%20these%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FU3rbi%2F1%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Child%20and%20adolescent%20mortality%20(in%20%25)%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20caveat%20here%20is%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Telangana%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Mizoram%20have%20less%20number%20of%20deprived%20households%20than%20Punjab%20but%20more%20than%20Goa.%20Sikkim%20is%20between%20Goa%20and%20Kerala.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMaternal%20care%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20household%20is%20defined%20as%20deprived%20in%20this%20category%20if%20there%20had%20been%20a%20woman%20in%20it%20who%20had%20given%20birth%20in%20the%20five%20years%20preceding%20the%20survey%20(NFHS-5)%20and%20had%20not%20received%20at%20least%20four%20antenatal%20care%20visits%20to%20the%20hospital%20before%20the%20birth%20of%20the%20child%3B%20or%20had%20not%20received%20assistance%20from%20trained%20and%20skilled%20medical%20personnel%20during%20the%20most%20recent%20childbirth.%20This%20indicator%20is%20not%20a%20part%20of%20the%20UN%20assessment%20of%20global%20multidimensional%20poverty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FKYNcW%2F2%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Maternal%20care%20(in%20%25)%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22185%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20caveat%20here%20is%2C%20Telangana%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Manipur%2C%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Mizoram%2C%20and%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20have%20lesser%20numbers%20of%20deprived%20households%20as%20compared%20to%20Punjab%2C%20but%20more%20than%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20maternal%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EEducation%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20indicators%20under%20this%20vertical.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EYears%20of%20schooling%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20household%20is%20deprived%20if%20not%20even%20one%20member%20of%20the%20household%20aged%2010%20years%20or%20older%20has%20completed%20six%20years%20of%20schooling%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NITI%20Aayog%20adds%20that%20this%20indicator%20has%20a%20cumulative%20positive%20effect%20on%20the%20household.%20%E2%80%9CEven%20if%20one%20member%20has%20more%20than%20six%20years%20of%20schooling%2C%20the%20positive%20effect%20of%20that%20education%20(in%20terms%20of%20an%20increase%20in%20economic%20opportunities%20such%20as%20the%20ability%20to%20enter%20high-paying%20employment%20or%20in%20terms%20of%20improvement%20in%20social%20standing)%20is%20shared%20among%20all%20members%20of%20the%20household%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20household%20had%20one%20member%20who%20had%20completed%20six%20years%20of%20schooling%2C%20the%20entire%20household%20is%20considered%20non-deprived%20%E2%80%93%20even%20if%20other%20members%20had%20not%20individually%20attended%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FQuJo7%2F1%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Years%20of%20schooling%20(in%20%25)%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20caveat%20is%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20proportions%20of%20households%20deprived%20under%20this%20indicator%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Manipur%20lie%20in%20between%20Punjab%20and%20Goa.%20Similarly%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20Uttarakhand%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20and%20Mizoram%20fare%20better%20than%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20but%20worse%20than%20Punjab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESchool%20attendance%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NITI%20Aayog%20considers%20a%20household%20as%20deprived%20if%20any%20school-aged%20child%20is%20not%20attending%20school%20up%20to%20the%20age%20at%20which%20s%2Fhe%20would%20complete%20Class%20VIII.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20says%20if%20a%20child%20is%20not%20doing%20so%2C%20it%20is%20indicative%20of%20the%20household%20experiencing%20difficulties%20not%20only%20in%20the%20present%20but%20also%20what%20it%20may%20experience%20in%20the%20future%20as%20a%20consequence%20of%20a%20child%20not%20completing%20education%20till%20Class%20VIII.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F5ug4c%2F1%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22School%20attendance%20(in%20%25)%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20caveat%20here%20is%2C%20lesser%20proportions%20of%20households%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20Mizoram%2C%20Tripura%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Manipur%2C%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Telangana%2C%20and%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20are%20deprived%20as%20compared%20to%20Punjab%2C%20but%20more%20than%20Tamil%20Nadu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EStandards%20of%20living%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20seven%20indicators%20under%20this%20vertical.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECooking%20fuel%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20household%20is%20deprived%20if%20the%20primary%20source%20of%20cooking%20fuel%20is%20dung%2C%20agricultural%20crops%2C%20shrubs%2C%20wood%2C%20charcoal%20or%20coal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20report%2C%20apart%20from%20having%20a%20clean%20source%20of%20cooking%2C%20the%20household%20also%20had%20to%20ensure%20that%20it%20was%20being%20utilised.%20The%20household%20must%20also%20be%20utilising%20the%20improved%2Fsafe%20source%20of%20cooking%20fuel%20as%20their%20primary%20source%20of%20cooking%20fuel%2C%20i.e.%20a%20household%20may%20have%20an%20LPG%20connection%20and%20stove%2C%20but%20if%20wood%2Fcoal%20is%20the%20primary%20(most%20used)%20fuel%20for%20cooking%2C%20then%20the%20house%20is%20considered%20deprived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Foog9E%2F1%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Cooking%20fuel%20(in%20%25)%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvidently%2C%20a%20lesser%20number%20of%20households%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Mizoram%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20Telangana%2C%20as%20compared%20to%20Sikkim%2C%20and%20more%20than%20Goa%2C%20were%20found%20deprived%20by%20the%20NITI%20Aayog.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESanitation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20household%20does%20not%20have%20a%20toilet%2C%20which%20is%20being%20utilised%20and%20is%20not%20shared%20with%20other%20households%2C%20it%20is%20considered%20to%20be%20deprived.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FAku1u%2F1%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Sanitation%20(in%20%25)%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20caveat%20here%20is%2C%20Nagaland%20and%20Mizoram%20have%20more%20deprivation%20than%20Goa%2C%20but%20less%20than%20Kerala.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETripura%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20Telangana%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Uttarakhand%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Meghalaya%20and%20Haryana%20lie%20between%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20Punjab%20on%20the%20charts%20as%20far%20as%20deprivation%20under%20this%20indicator%20is%20concerned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDrinking%20water%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NITI%20Aayog%20says%20a%20household%20would%20be%20marked%20deprived%20if%20it%20does%20not%20have%20access%20to%20an%20improved%20source%20of%20safe%20drinking%20water%2C%20or%20if%20the%20access%20to%20safe%20drinking%20water%20takes%20more%20than%20a%2030-minute%20walk%20from%20home%20(as%20a%20round%20trip).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22ht