rs%20is%20nothing%20new%2C%20and%20in%20fact%2C%20pirate%20attacks%20are%20generally%20on%20the%20decline%2C%20with%202022%20seeing%20the%20lowest%20number%20of%20piracy%20incidents%20since%201994%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icc-ccs.org%2Findex.php%2F1324-sustained-efforts-needed-as-global-piracy-incidents-hit-lowest-levels-in-decades%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%20from%20International%20Maritime%20Bureau.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20McKnight%2C%20who%20was%20the%20first%20commander%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcombinedmaritimeforces.com%2Fctf-151-counter-piracy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20international%20anti-piracy%20task%20force%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20the%20problem%20of%20piracy%20is%20unlikely%20to%20ever%20be%20entirely%20eradicated.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20long%20as%20ships%20go%20to%20sea%2C%20there's%20gonna%20be%20piracy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20'wild%2C%20wild%20West'%20on%20the%20open%20seas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMcKnight%2C%20who%20oversaw%20Combined%20Task%20Force%20151%20for%20five%20months%20in%202009%2C%20said%20the%20multinational%20counter-piracy%20task%20force%20was%20created%20to%20address%20the%20increasing%20issue%20of%20maritime%20piracy%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Somalia%20that%20exploded%20in%20the%20mid-to-late%20aughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20%26quot%3Bpirates%26quot%3B%20would%20capture%20vessels%20in%20international%20waters%20and%20bring%20them%20back%20into%20territorial%20waters%20%E2%80%94%20the%20seas%20up%20to%2012%20miles%20surrounding%20a%20sovereign%20state%20in%20which%20no%20other%20authorities%20have%20jurisdiction%20%E2%80%94%20to%20avoid%20being%20apprehended%2C%20McKnight%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Gulf%20of%20Aden%2C%20located%20between%20Yemen%20to%20the%20north%20and%20Somalia%20to%20the%20south%2C%20became%20a%20prime%20piracy%20spot%20amid%20the%20surge%20thanks%20to%20its%20status%20as%20a%20massive%20trade%20route%20that%20sees%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20081204080826%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fnews.yahoo.com%2Fs%2Fap%2F20081202%2Fap_on_re_af%2Fpiracy%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2020%2C000%20merchant%20ships%3C%2Fa%3E%20pass%20through%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228660%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20map%20of%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Aden.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c05fb2671ed600191529b5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225773%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20map%20of%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Aden.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20wild%2C%20wild%20West%20out%20there.%20There%20are%20hundreds%20of%20dhows%20either%20smuggling%20arms%2C%20drugs%2C%20or%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20McKnight%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20narrow%20ships%20that%20often%20operate%20without%20an%20identification%20signal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERampant%20drug%20trafficking%20throughout%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Aden%20has%20spawned%20a%20biting%20nickname%20for%20the%20waterway%20%E2%80%94%20the%20hash%20highway%20%E2%80%94%20and%20weapons%20are%20often%20carried%20from%20Africa%20to%20Yemen%20on%20its%20seas%2C%20McKnight%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20trying%20to%20pick%20a%20needle%20out%20of%20a%20haystack%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20apprehending%20traffickers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBoarding%20parties%20can%20bring%20danger%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20of%20intercepting%20illegal%20goods%20on%20the%20open%20ocean%20is%20a%20laborious%20one%2C%20McKnight%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECiting%20his%20own%20experience%20commanding%20the%20still%20operational%20anti-piracy%20task%20force%2C%20McKnight%20said%20officials%20will%20usually%20go%20after%20a%20vessel%20only%20after%20they%20have%20sufficient%20inte