rl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fsag-aftra-strike-publicsts-panic-fall-film-festivals-1235680017%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fsag-aftra-strike-publicsts-panic-fall-film-festivals-1235680017%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Support%20for%20using%20violence%20to%20'coerce'%20members%20of%20Congress%20nearly%20doubled%20over%20the%20last%206%20months%20%E2%80%94%20even%20more%20so%20among%20Democrats%20%E2%80%94%20according%20to%20a%20study%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223915%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Thunderstorm%20clouds%20roll%20over%20the%20US%20Capitol.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F646ed57450731c001938ad85%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221957%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThunderstorm%20clouds%20roll%20over%20the%20US%20Capitol.%3Cp%3EChip%20Somodevilla%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20recent%20study%20found%20that%20public%20support%20for%20using%20violence%20to%20%26quot%3Bcoerce%26quot%3B%20members%20of%20Congress%20nearly%20doubled%20from%20January%20to%20June.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESupport%20among%20self-identified%20Democrats%20for%20political%20violence%20grew%20by%20about%20250%25%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20there's%20distrust%20in%20democracy%2C%20the%20more%20that's%20leading%20to%20radical%20support%20for%20the%20use%20of%20force%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study's%20author%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPublic%20support%20for%20the%20use%20of%20force%20against%20members%20of%20Congress%20nearly%20doubled%20from%20January%20to%20June%20of%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20a%20recent%20study%20shared%20with%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20published%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago's%20Project%20on%20Security%20and%20Threats%20(CPOST)%2C%20found%20that%20as%20of%20June%2026%2C%2017%25%20of%20the%20American%20public%20%E2%80%94%20an%20estimated%2044%20million%20people%20%E2%80%94%20supported%20using%20violence%20to%20coerce%20lawmakers.%20That's%20up%20from%209%25%20when%20the%20survey%20was%20conducted%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spike%20was%20most%20pronounced%20among%20self-identified%20Democrats%3A%20in%20January%2C%207%25%20of%20Democrats%20supported%20using%20political%20violence%20against%20lawmakers%2C%20and%20that%20number%20climbed%20to%2016%25%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20contrast%2C%20the%20support%20for%20political%20violence%20against%20Congress%20among%20self-identifying%20Republicans%20increased%20by%2050%25.%20Overall%2C%20a%20higher%20percentage%20of%20these%20Republicans%20%E2%80%94%2018%25%20of%20all%20respondents%20%E2%80%94%20endorse%20the%20use%20of%20force%20against%20lawmakers%20compared%20to%20Democrats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20say%20violence%20or%20coercion%2C%20we're%20using%20'use%20of%20force'%20specifically%20because%20we%20know%20the%20respondents%20interpret%20that%20as%20meaning%2C%20'even%20if%20some%20people%20are%20injured%20and%20killed%2C'%26quot%3B%20Robert%20Pape%2C%20a%20political%20science%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%20and%20the%20study's%20author%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20while%20support%20for%20violence%20against%20members%20of%20Congress%20increased%20%26quot%3Bacross%20the%20political%20spectrum%2C%20the%20rise%20was%20sharpest%20among%20Democrats%2C%20where%20it%20grew%20by%20about%202.5%20times.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20did%20not%20draw%20a%20specific%20causal%20link%20for%20the%20rise%20in%20support%20for%20extremism%20among%20Democrats%2C%20but%20noted%20that%20it%20coincides%20with%20%26quot%3Bgrowing%20anger%20over%20the%20Republican-controlled%20House%20of%20Representatives%20and%20hearings%20that%20they%20have%20held%20painting%20a%20disparaging%20picture%20of%20Democrats.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPape's%20report%2C%20which%20was%20published%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20also%20clocked%20a%20significant%20jump%20over%20the%20last%20several%20months%20in%20public%20support%20for%20using%20violence%20to%20restore%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecifically%2C%20the%20survey%20found%20roughly%204%25%20of%20Americans%20%E2%80%94%20an%20estimated%2012%20million%20people%20%E2%80%94%20supported%20using%20violence%20to%20return%20Trump%20to%20office%20in%20April.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20June%2C%20that%20number%20spiked%20to%20an%20estimated%2018%20million%20Americans%2C%20about%20a%2050%25%20increase.%20The%20CPOST%20survey%20polled%203%2C543%20adults%20between%20June%2022%20and%20June%2026%20had%20a%202.3%25%20margin%20of%20error.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPape%20also%20noted%20that%20rise%20in%20radical%20support%20for%20violence%20across%20the%20aisle%20is%20connected%20to%20%26quot%3Bperceived%20corruption%20in%20our%20democratic%20institutions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20credible%20evidence%20that%20the%20more%20there's%20distrust%20in%20democracy%2C%20the%20more%20that's%20leading%20to%20radical%20support%20for%20the%20use%20of%20force%20for%20both%20conservative%2C%20Republican%20causes%20and%20also%20for%20liberal%20causes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpublic-support-violence-coerce-congress-doubled-over-6-months-study-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690323182000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F647e14dba52c4b001936a375%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpublic-support-violence-coerce-congress-doubled-over-6-months-study-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BThe%20more%20there's%20distrust%20in%20democracy%2C%20the%20more%2