p%2Fbooks%2Fbook%2Fchicago%2FA%2Fbo3628811.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20recalled%20how%20easy%20it%20was%20to%20get%20lost%20because%20all%20the%20buildings%20looked%20alike%2C%20painted%20the%20same%20green%2C%20and%20there%20were%20no%20street%20names.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%20the%20Manhattan%20Project%2C%20workers%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.aip.org%2Faapt%2Fajp%2Farticle%2F88%2F12%2F1175%2F859737%2FManhattan-Project-The-Story-of-the-Century-Bruce%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewould%20construct%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20600%20housing%20units%2C%20including%20dozens%20of%20dormitories%20and%20barracks%20for%20unmarried%20personnel%20and%20the%20military.%20There%20were%20also%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fahf.nuclearmuseum.org%2Fvoices%2Foral-histories%2Fanna-mae-gillespies-interview%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edorms%20for%20married%20couples%3C%2Fa%3E%20whose%20jobs%20weren't%20as%20well-paid%20as%20the%20scientists'.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20coveted%20houses%20were%20originally%20part%20of%20the%20school.%20They%20came%20to%20be%20nicknamed%20%26quot%3BBathtub%20Row%26quot%3B%20because%20the%20newer%20houses%20only%20had%20showers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20were%20attractive%2C%20well-built%20cottages%2C%20far%20more%20desirable%20than%20any%20later%20building%2C%26quot%3B%20Laura%20Fermi%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20homes'%20residents%2C%20including%20Oppenheimer%2C%20lent%20a%20certain%20cach%C3%A9%20to%20the%20area%2C%20too.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECreating%20a%20small%20city%20required%20more%20than%20just%20housing.%20Schools%2C%20courts%2C%20stores%2C%20a%20post%20office%2C%20a%20fire%20department%2C%20and%20a%20hospital%20all%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.aip.org%2Faapt%2Fajp%2Farticle%2F88%2F12%2F1175%2F859737%2FManhattan-Project-The-Story-of-the-Century-Bruce%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeventually%20appeared%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Los%20Alamos%20also%20needed%20veterinarians%20for%20the%20Military%20Police's%20horses%2C%20dentists%2C%20doctors%2C%20and%20garbage%20collectors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3BTechnical%20Area%26quot%3B%20was%20a%20top-secret%20space%20that%20required%20workers%20to%20show%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FAtomic_Spaces%2Fr7zvAAAAMAAJ%3Fhl%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Especial%20badge%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F25637414%3Fmag%3Dlos-alamos-secret-library%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eguard%20house%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Administrative%20buildings%2C%20labs%2C%20and%20warehouses%20clustered%20around%20a%20pond%20where%20the%20school's%20students%20used%20to%20ice%20skate.%20All%20were%20sequestered%20behind%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.osti.gov%2Fopennet%2Fmanhattan-project-history%2FPlaces%2FLosAlamos%2Ftech-area.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echain-link%20fence%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPhysicist%20McAllister%20Hull%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FRider_of_the_Pale_Horse%2FddOhAwAAQBAJ%3Fhl%3Den%26gbpv%3D1%26dq%3D%2522los%2Balamos%2522%2B%2522fences%2Bwithin%2Bfences%2522%26pg%3DPA26%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edescribed%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%26quot%3Bfences%20within%20fences%26quot%3B%20because%20the%20entire%20site%20was%20enclosed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESecrecy%20was%20paramount%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20adjusting%20to%20life%20at%20Los%20Alamos%20was%20getting%20used%20to%20all%20the%20secrecy.%20New%20arrivals%20were%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com.gi%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DBWek8zJ-U7IC%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%26rview%3D1%26source%3Dgbs_vpt_read%23v%3Donepage%26q%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efingerprinted%20and%20photographed%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20received%20New%20Mexico%20driver's%20licenses.%20Their%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.penguinrandomhouse.com%2Fbooks%2F60762%2Fgenius-by-james-gleick%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enames%20were%20listed%20as%20numbers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20signatures%20weren't%20required%2C%20and%20instead%20of%20an%20address%2C%20they%20read%2C%20%26quot%3BSpecial%20List%20B.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Several%20people%20enter%20and%20exist%20the%20entrance%20to%20the%20technical%20area%20at%20Los%20Alamos%20in%201951%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64c02dfcbea34400196188e9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20entrance%20to%20the%20Los%20Alamos%20lab's%20Tech%20Area%20in%201951.%3Cp%3ENational%20Security%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20incoming%20and%20outgoing%20mail%20went%20through%20censors.%20Correspondents%20had%20to%20address%20letters%20to%20P.O.%20Box%201663.%20Residents'%20mail%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F25637414%3Fmag%3Dlos-alamos-secret-library%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erouted%20through%20another%20town%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20being%20sent%20to%20friends%20and%20family.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERichard%20Feynman's%20wife%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcalteches.library.caltech.edu%2F34%2F3%2FFeynmanLosAlamos.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esent%20him%20a%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20complaining%20about%20the%20censors%20watching.%20Officials%20told%20him%20to%20ask%20her%20not%20to%20mention%20censorship.%20When%20he%20did%2C%20they%20returned%20his%20letter%20and%20said%20he%20had%20to%20inform%20her%20without%20mentioning%20censorship%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20in%20the%20heck%20am%20I%20going%20to%20do%20it%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.taylorfrancis.com%2Fchapters%2Fedit%2F10.4324%2F9781351302005-11%2Fpapa-bomb-carol-wolkowitz%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20age%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Los%20Alamos'%20residents%20was%20mid-20s.%20For%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lanl.gov%2Fmuseum%2Fnews%2Fnewsletter%2F2017%2F2017-01%2Fscience-question-babies.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E80%20babies%3C%2Fa%3E%20born%20in%20the%20project's%20first%20year%2C%20the%20same%20P.O.%20box%20number%20where%20their%20mail%20was%20sent%20was%20also%20put%20on%20their%20birth%20certificates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20poem%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FManhattan_Project%2F9v_oDwAAQBAJ%3Fhl%3Den%26gbpv%3D1%26dq%3D%25E2%2580%259CHe%2Bthought%2Byou%2527d%2Bbe%2Bscientific%2B%2F%2BInstead%2Byou%2527re%2Bjust%2Bprolific.%25E2%2580%259D%26pg%3DPA240%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoked%20fun%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Groves'%20annoyance%20at%20the%20number%20of%20newborns%3A%20%26quot%3BHe%20thought%20you'd%20be%20scientific%20%2F%20Instead%20you're%20just%20prolific.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%20days%2C%20physicist%20Robert%20Serber%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.aip.org%2Faapt%2Fajp%2Farticle%2F88%2F12%2F1175%2F859737%2FManhattan-Project-The-Story-of-the-Century-Bruce%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edelivered%20an%20orientation%20lecture%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20about%2030%20people%20about%20the%20project.%20Carpenters%20and%20electricians%20were%20hard%20at%20work.%20When%20Serber%20mentioned%20the%20bomb%2C%20Oppenheimer%20instructed%20John%20Manley%20to%20tell%20Serber%20to%20say%20%26quot%3Bgadget%26quot%3B%20in%20case%20the%20workers%20overheard.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFatigue%20and%20fighting%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20memoirs%20and%20interviews%2C%20some%20scientists'%20wives%20claimed%20not%20to%20have%20known%20what%20their%20husbands%20were%20working%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeon%20Fisher%20brought%20red%20and%20green%20detonator%20casings%20home%20for%20his%20child%20to%20play%20with.%20Phyllis%2C%20his%20wife%2C%20used%20them%20to%20trim%20a%20Christmas%20tree.%20Later%2C%20she%20reflected%20on%20the%20irony%20of%20decorating%20an%20evergreen%2C%20a%20symbol%20of%20renewal%2C%20with%20%26quot%3Bmessengers%20of%20death.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIgnorance%20had%20sanctioned%20that%20strange%20combination%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnsuworks.nova.edu%2Fpcs%2Fvol15%2Fiss2%2F3%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20secrecy%2C%20the%20stress%2C%20and%20the%20long%20hours%20all%20contributed%20to%20a%20tense%20atmosphere%20that%20could%20set%20everyone%20on%20edge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRank%2C%20housing%20assignments%2C%20the%20part%20of%20town%20in%20which%20one%20lived%2C%20social%20invitations%2C%20administrative%20assignments%2C%20everything%20became%20important%2C%20occasionally%20in%20a%20childish%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Emile%20Segr%C3%A9%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublishing.cdlib.org%2Fucpressebooks%2Fview%3FdocId%3Dft700007rb%3Bquery%3D%3Bbrand%3Ducpress%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elater%20wrote%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20atmosphere%20also%20strained%20marriages.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20past%2C%20Leon%20had%20always%20patiently%20described%20his%20scientific%20projects%20or%20research%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Phyllis%20Fisher%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F